y</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Double Attacking</span><hr size=1> What skill does one raise to double attack?  I see NPCs doing it quite often with Melee Attacks.  Is this just lag?  Or can you do it?<br>
<br>
<br>
-Ciciro &quot;Tittle&quot; Lree- <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=jaqrabbit>Jaqrabbit</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#660000>(11/14/02 4:28 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://members.cox.net/ccallahan3/radiohead.gif WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Double Attacking</span><hr size=1> If you're talking about what I think you're talking about, it's just lag.  Sometimes the server thinks you should be attacking at at different time than your client does, and you see two attacks, only one of which will do damage (the other is just an animation). <p>~Jaqrabbit<br>
&quot;It's a trick... Get an axe.&quot;<br>
