I am the master of my fate: I am the captain of my soul.&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iccusion>iccusion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 176<br> <font color=#660000>(11/15/02 2:25 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re: Double Attack</span><hr size=1> <!--EZCODE QUOTE START--><blockquote><strong><em>Quote:</em></strong><hr>&quot;That happened cuz of the v16.0 patch. It messed up mobs so that they hit twice with one move (only melee mobs though). <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong><!--EZCODE ITALIC START--><em>They fixed it in one of the following patchs I believe, so it may be lag for you.</em><!--EZCODE ITALIC END--></strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->&quot;<hr></blockquote><!--EZCODE QUOTE END-->Well, they didn't COMPLETELY fix it.<br>
<br>
They were supposed to, but in their usual style, FC implemented a not-fully-successful fix.  I still get the occasional mobs that do double melee hits, and my engie alt's bot still does PRIMARILY double hits.  Sync issues (which were already bad <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>before</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> 14.6) are now horrific.  After killing a mob, I TYPICALLY have to wait an extra 5-10 seconds until I get xp and the mob finally dies on my screen and allows me to loot.  But the client KNOWS the mob is dead, because my attack turns off and if I try to attack some more, it says &quot;target is already dead&quot;.  And yet there it is...wailing away at me.  All this with DSL and a &lt;50ms ping.<br>
<br>
I especially LOVE 14.6's extra 10-20 seconds of NOTHING BUT A BLANK SCREEN when I try to zone into a crowded zone like Newland, Tir, or Omni Trade/Ent now.  The first couple times this happened, I thought my PC had locked up...I was about to hit Ctrl-Alt-Delete when I FINALLY zoned in.  Ye gods.<br>
<br>
I tell ya, FunCom better hire some damn programmers.  This crap is getting WORSE, not better.<br>
<br>
- iccusion<br>
<br>
