<br>
Be EXTRA careful when fighting any melee mob (enforcers, or non-human monster-types).<br>
<br>
I especially love that all the new NPC mob pets in missions get this lovely double attack.  Because you know, that opening room with 3 Master Robotbuilders and their 3 slayerdroid pets wasn't really hard enough without the slayers getting double hits...  *rolls eyes*<br>
<br>
- iccusion <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#FFFFCC><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=alectosf>AlectoSF</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Training Dummy</span><br>  Posts: 95<br> <font color=#660000>(11/20/02 2:06 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re: Double Attack</span><hr size=1> Hasn't this always been the case with creature NPCs?<br>
<br>
My MP's pets (meatballs) have always double hit, so I'd expect meatball NPC MP pets to do likewise (not that I'd enjoy it; my MPs pets are unreal). <br>
<br>
As for humanoid NPCs, well, that's not good. Not good at all, at all... <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#99CC66><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub83.ezboard.com/bthepunchingbag74708.showUserPublicProfile?gid=iccusion>iccusion</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Peking Duck</span><br>  Posts: 183<br> <font color=#660000>(11/20/02 4:08 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=8>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Re: Double Attack</span><hr size=1> Yes and no.  This is not a new bug, but it is now a more consistent bug.<br>
<br>
Before 14.6, there were several <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>creature</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> mobs that double hit, including player's pets.  Now it is pretty much <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><strong>all</strong><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> melee mobs, even the already brutal HUMAN enforcer-type NPC mobs.  And of course, now we have the lovely mission pets...and they all get double hits, too.<br>
<br>
It used to be that you would only encounter this problem when you came across a Manteze or an Anun or another such melee monster.  Now it can be any melee mob.<br>
<br>
- iccusion <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table> </td></tr></table> <table border=0 width=95%><tr><td align=left valign="top"> </td><td align=right valign="top"><a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showPrevMessage?topicID=2152.topic"> << Prev Topic</a>&nbsp;| <a href="http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showNextMessage?topicID=2152.topic"> Next Topic >> </a><br><br><a self href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=2152.topic&index=8><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/addReply.gif border=0 alt="Add Reply"></a> </td></tr></table><br><table width=95% border=0><td valign="top"> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.emailToFriend?topicID=2152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/image/email.gif border=0 alt="Email This To a Friend"> Email This To a Friend</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.threadControl?topicID=2152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/far_east/deleteThread.gif border=0 alt="Topic Control Image"> Topic Commands</a><br> <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.subscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/subscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to receive email notification of replies"> Click to receive email notification of replies</a> <br>  <a href=http://pub83.ezboard.com/fthepunchingbag74708frm1.unsubscribeUnregisteredToTopic?topicID=2152.topic><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/themes/ultimate/unsubscribe.gif width=20 height=20 border=0 alt="Click to stop receiving email notification of replies"> Click to stop receiving email notification of replies</a> <br> </td><td align="right" valign="top"></td></tr><tr align="right"><td colspan=2><form action=http://pub83.ezboard.com/BBSForum.jumpShowForum method=post><table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="1"><tr><td><b>jump to:</